question:
Given the multi-process program below, which of the following are infeasible output(s) of the program?
PS: fflush(stdout) is a function to flush the standard output immediately, so that before the next printf() is invoked, the output buffer is empty.
int main()
{
   printf("A"); fflush(stdout);
   if (fork() == 0){
     printf("B"); fflush(stdout);
     if (fork() == 0){
       printf("C"); fflush(stdout);
       exit(1);
     }
     printf("D"); fflush(stdout);
     exit(2);
   }
   printf("C"); fflush(stdout);
   exit(0);
}

